description: Milan Rabij was born on 8th March 1999 in Katowice. At the age of 7 he started percussion instruments education in the Stanisław Moniuszko Primary State Music School in Katowice. At the age of 8 he started learning how to play on drumset in one of drum schools. When he was 12, he became the youngest finalist of Mapex Drummer of Tomorrow competition. Year later he composed soundtrack to the documentary ''Bones'' which as a part of an multimedia book ''Death'', has been released all over the world. At the age of 15 he got Grand Prix and first prize in two polish national percussion competitions. At the age of 16 he ended his debut album ''Twenty Hidden Bodies'' with his band You Know What. He continues learning in percussion instruments class in The Karol Szymanowski Secondary State Music School in Katowice. Milan also runs his channel on YouTube and an official website on which you can get extra information about him as well as talk about the cooperation.

description:
Imagine what the world would look like if you can stretch a 1 second action in 40 seconds.  To do so require specialized cameras that can shoot a minimum of 1000 frames per second.  Yes, 1000 photographs in a single second.    These photographs are stitched together to create super slow motion video.  

To watch such 1 second events in slow motion expands your mind and I assure you - it will relieve stress as well.  So please slow down with me and watch the videos in its fullest.  

While you will see that the natural world dominates the videos, there will be studio shots as well.  

Please watch with audio and in large screen for enhanced viewing experience.
Please DM me for any related business opportunities.
Massachusetts, USA.
#rmslowmotion

description:
Hi everyone,
My name is Mightnare, I'm an old school gamer who has returned to gaming community.
I'm planning to play video games from multiple platforms.

Since I'm an old school gamer, I've 3 main goals on my channel:
1- Introducing old games to new generations, so they can catch up to the fun they've missed, and giving nostalgic vibes to my fellow old school gamers, and triggering their childhood's good memories too.
2- Featuring not only retro old games, but also new ones (If they are good).
3- I don't necessarily follow what's trending; I only appreciate the great games and I post videos about them, despite being new games or old games.

IMPORTANT NOTE:
In my recent videos, I deliberately didn't want to be a perfectionist who seeks 100% completion of any game walkthrough, because that defeats the main purpose of gaming (entertainment)
This approach is meant to encourage all of you to ONLY ENJOY GAMES, instead of grinding for unnecessary achievements that waste your precious time.

description:
Somos “Gamers”
Um termo que surgiu e começou a ser usado após a popularização dos videogames e PCs para jogos. Gamer é literalmente “aquele que joga”, sendo atualmente o termo principal quando o assunto são produtos dedicados a jogadores. Sendo assim, qualquer um que jogue independente da plataforma pode se considerar um “Gamer”, porque jogar transcende plataformas, e não importa se somos “noobs”, jogadores casuais, jogadores “hardcore” ou atletas eletrônicos, pois jogar é parte do nosso entretenimento, do nosso trabalho e da nossa vida.

Somos Tech
Trazemos vários conteúdos de tecnologia e o melhor do mundo Tech, além de ser referência no mundo dos Hardwares, sempre ajudamos a aqueles que estão iniciando nesse mundo tecnológico!

Are you new to sports videography and not sure where to start? Beyond the Game is a source of educational sports videography content giving you the tools and knowledge you need to create epic sports videos and ultimately achieve your dream of working alongside the athletes you idolize.

A little bit about me... After 6 years producing content for NHL, NBA, and UFC live events, I left it all behind me and decided to follow my heart and move to Australia for love. I still had a passion for sports videography though, so I quickly started learning as much as I could about Australian sports and the Australian sports industry. The next thing you know, I was producing video content for sport clubs, federations, leagues and promoters all over the country while documenting my journey on this channel.

Subscribe for weekly videos! :)

description: Welcome to KöhlerSAStudios, I am orginally from South Africa 🇿🇦 and a descendant of Germany 🇩🇪. description:
Are you into miniature engines, retro-technologies, nerdy experiments and forgotten science and math? This retro-themed STEM channel is for you!

This channel presents retro-themed technologies and material of a generally nerdy nature: many kinds of demonstration engines, forgotten math from the pre (or early) digital age, clever contraptions, retro-style engineering and mind-boggling physical principles and phenomena.

I'm a professional software developer and I work (among other things) with robotics, computer vision and machine learning. But I have always been a fan of all kinds of science, technology and engineering.
